<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be a back seat driver • be in the back seat</xh5><p> <i>be a back seat driver—</i>suggest unwanted advice; tell a person in charge how to do his job: It is always easy to criticize and <u>be a back seat driver</u>.</p><p> <i>be in the back seat</i>—(also: take a back seat) take a subordinate position: Dad <u>is now in the back seat</u>. Jonathan is in control of the Rowland Capital family trust.</p> </entry>
